description: Bullets. Ammo for the Machinegun and Chaingun weapons.
Cells. Ammo for the Hyperblaster and BFG10K, and power for the Power Shield and Power Screen.
Grenades. Ammo for the Grenade Launcher. Can also be thrown individually.
A-M Bomb. In SP: a key objective. In MP: a nuke that cleanses anything in a big radius, regardless of walls.
Rockets. Ammo for the Rocket Launcher.
Shells. Ammo for the Shotgun and Super Shotgun.
Tesla Mine. Launches a small base that electrocutes anything it comes into contact with.
Tag token for deathmatch tag games.
An invisible object that divides the world into areas that are separated when this portal is dormant. Usually enclosed in the middle of a door.
A button. When touched, it moves some distance in the direction of its angle, triggers all of its targets, waits some time, and returns into its original position, so it can be triggered again.

description: A clock. Can be triggered, or start at the beginning of the level. Must be used in tandem with target_characters and/or target_string.
OBSOLETE. Use func_train instead. A stationary brush that moves whatever is non them. Needs at least one ''current content'' enabled. (?)

description: EDITOR-ONLY. Groups brushes for many tasks.
A brush that kills everything inside of it. Must be triggered in order to work. Ignores all kinds of protection.
Object that falls down when triggered.

An elevating platform. These are always drawn in the extended position so they will light correctly. If it's in the tatget of another trigger/button, starts out disabled in the extended position until triggered.

quaked: /* QUAKED func_plat2 (0 .5 .8) ? PLAT_LOW_TRIGGER PLAT2_TOGGLE PLAT2_TOP PLAT2_TRIGGER_TOP PLAT2_TRIGGER_BOTTOM BOX_LIFT

description: A timer. Once a certain amount of time passed, it triggers all of its targets and restarts.

Moving, rideable platform. The train follows a set of path_corner that are used for its trajectory, with a small origin brush determining the ''railing'' point of the train. The train spawns in the first target it's pointing at. If the train is the target of a button or trigger, it won't move until triggered.

quaked: /* QUAKED func_wall (0 .5 .8) ? TRIGGER_SPAWN TOGGLE START_ON ANIMATED ANIMATED_FAST
description: Triggerable solid wall. Can materialize out of thin air and vanish. Used mostly for forcefields and monster closets.
Movable target brush that must be targeted in order to operate. It's recommended to use a texture with liquid properties.
Gets the monsters to walk around the map.
Positional target for target_laser, turret_breach and teleporter_destination.
Potential spawning position for coop games with a lava level that needs to be checked such as rmine2.
Adrenaline. Restores health and adds 1HP permanently in SP.
Bandolier. Extends the ammunition count for all weapons except grenades and rockets.
Rebreather. Allows players to breathe in water areas for a certain period of time.
Double Damage. Multiplies weapon damage. Can Stack with Quad Damage.
Environment Suit. Provides protection from slime areas.
Large Health. Provides 25 HP when collected.
Megahealth. Provides 100 HP when collected. The health from this item overstacks.
Medium Health. Provides 10 HP when collected.
Stimpack. Provides 5 HP when collected. The health from this item overstacks.
Invulnerability. Offers protection against anything that isn't the void or a death pit.
Ammo Pack. Extends the ammunition count for all weapons.
Power Screen. Offers frontal partial protection from damage. Consumes cells.
Power Shield. Offers full-body partial protection from damage. Consumes cells.
Silencer. Silences the player and its weapon fire.
Defender Sphere. Sentinel sphere that shoots anything that seeks to kill the player.
Hunter Sphere. MP item that chases enemies who attack the player.
Vengeance Sphere. MP item that chases enemies who fragged the player.
Predefined light source with a model attached on it.
Predefined light source with a model attached on it.

description: Dead Soldier. Does nothing except be gibbed on fire. Must be placed on the floor, otherwise it will float!

quaked: /* QUAKED misc_insane (1 .5 0) (-16 -16 -24) (16 16 32) Ambush Trigger_Spawn CRAWL CRUCIFIED STAND_GROUND ALWAYS_STAND
description: Insane soldier. Begs to be killed. Can't be rescued. Can follow (optionally) a path set with path_corners.
Satellite Dish. Can be placed as a static decoration (space) or triggered, in whose case it will tilt up and rotate to the left (base3).
Teleporter. Teleports the player to a certain location. Must be used in tandem with misc_teleporter_dest.
Teleporter destination. Must be the target of a misc_teleporter.
Viper Bomber. Drops bombs into an area marked previously with key_airstrike_target.
DECORATION ONLY. Standing, invulnerable Jorg (boss1). For the real thing use monster_jorg.
DECORATION ONLY. Tank Commander's body. Usually located near a Commander's Head. For the real thing use instead monster_tank_commander.
Medic Commander. Heals and spawns other monsters.

description: Path corner. Used mostly for func_trains and trigger_elevator-triggered func_plat. Also controls the patrol routes of monsters, misc_insanes, misc_vipers, misc_bigvipers and misc_strogg_ships.

Combat points for monsters. A monster which is engaging the player will stop at this point and use their ranged attack. Can be linked in order to form a network that the monster will travel. Afterwards they will chase the player.
Causes an entity to be angry at another entity.
Pulsing black light with sphere in the center.
Blaster fire. Must be triggered in order to work.
One of eight 8x16 brushes required for the style of a func_clock to work.

description: Targeted event of a target_crosslevel_trigger in SP.

description: Triggers up to eight events in another level of the unit in SP.
An earthquake. Must be triggered in order to work.
Creates a visual explosion that can inflict damage.
Goal target. When the map is being loaded in SP, the game counts all of them. When a goal has been triggered, it adds 1 to the goal count.
Computer updater target. Updates the help computer in SP.
Kills all the players on the map. God-mode proof.

description: Laser that inflicts damage. Moving lasers must be targeted to func_train.
Target that makes a light fade in/out.
Secret target. When the map is being loaded in SP, the game counts all of them. When a secret has been triggered, it adds 1 to the secret count.
Spawns another entity. Can be an item or a monster.
Plays a sound in a particular area.
Spawns liquid splashes in an area.
Entity that allows func_clock to use target_characters.
Trigger that activates at the beginning of the level.
Trigger that activates when two or more actions take place. (I.E. a door that opens with two buttons)
Trigger that puts a disguise in any player that uses it. The disguise is destroyed upon weapon fire.
Elevator trigger. Used in elevators that span multiple levels such as the lava room one in ''Borehole'' (mine2). Must be used in tandem with func_button and func_train (and ofc path_corner).
Trigger that affects the gravity of anything inside of it.

description: Trigger that damages anything inside of it.
Trigger that requires a key_ item in order to be operated.
Entity that can only be triggered by a monster. Makes the monster jump over something.

description: Trigger that can be activated multiple times.
Trigger that can be activated only once.
Trigger that pushes the player in any direction. Used for wind tunnels.

description: Trigger that teleports any player that touches it.
Invisible brain that drives the turret.
Disintegrator. Cut weapon that disintegrates an enemy.
ETF Rifle. Shoots flechettes that ignore armor.
Plasma Beam. Shoots a plasma stream that cooks anything it touches.
Prox Launcher. Shoots mines that explode upon proximity.
Main world entity. All maps have one.
